You actually might as well just do BCBA because to sit for the exam you must acquire supervision hours and have added ABA as a minor . The pay jump is 16-22 to 30-35 an hour so you wouldn’t have to work as long while studying but it’ll take at least 2 semesters and the 6 months of getting supervised hours. You should be looking in if you need supervised hours to sit in for the BCBA moving forward. 

P.S. - I know we all want success and can’t wait to get it but be weary of putting too much on your plate while being an RBT or when doing anything that deals with helping other people . With this field it’s easy to get burn out and it comes easy when we aren’t having time for ourselves after we leave our spectrum babies. Just remember to breathe and recenter, there’s no rush.
